WEBVTT

00:03.803 --> 00:05.472
[BRIGHT TONE]

00:07.740 --> 00:09.475
[CAMERA BEEPS]

00:09.508 --> 00:12.711
[MIC THUDS]

00:12.745 --> 00:15.047
WOMAN:<i> Some of these questions
might be difficult to answer,</i>

00:15.081 --> 00:16.482
<i> but just take your time,</i>

00:16.515 --> 00:19.051
<i> and let us know
if you need a break, okay?</i>

00:19.085 --> 00:21.187
<i> Clay, you're here today</i>

00:21.221 --> 00:24.257
<i> to set the record straight
about your father.</i>

00:24.290 --> 00:26.525
<i> But first, this has been
a really rough year for you,</i>

00:26.559 --> 00:27.527
<i> with the accident.</i>

00:27.560 --> 00:29.629
<i> How are you coping?</i>

00:29.662 --> 00:32.065
Yeah, um, it's...

00:34.467 --> 00:36.403
It's been hard.

00:36.436 --> 00:39.339
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

00:45.311 --> 00:48.314
CLAY:<i> In, like, a second
everything changed.</i>

00:50.883 --> 00:53.820
[LOW RUMBLING]

00:55.755 --> 00:57.223
[METAL CREAKING]

00:57.256 --> 00:58.324
<i> People come up to me,</i>

00:58.357 --> 01:00.359
<i> and they tell me
that I'm brave,</i>

01:00.393 --> 01:01.861
<i> like this was a choice.</i>

01:01.894 --> 01:03.696
[TRUCK RATTLING]

01:03.729 --> 01:04.864
<i> Like I'm gonna get better.</i>

01:04.898 --> 01:06.933
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

01:06.966 --> 01:08.534
CLAY:
<i> But that's not how it works.</i>

01:08.568 --> 01:10.537
[GASPING]

01:10.570 --> 01:13.473
[CREAKING STOPS]

01:17.176 --> 01:20.313
[METAL CREAKING]

01:24.183 --> 01:27.320
[CREAKING STOPS]

01:32.258 --> 01:33.792
CLAY:
<i> This chair feels like a...</i>

01:33.826 --> 01:36.729
[LAUGHS]
<i> A goddamn prison.</i>

01:41.233 --> 01:44.704
<i>And I'm not sure what the hell
I'm supposed to do.</i>

01:52.245 --> 01:54.314
<i> My dad would know.</i>

01:57.850 --> 02:00.587
[LIGHTER CLICKS OFF]

02:00.620 --> 02:03.223
<i> That's the thing.
He was always there for me.</i>

02:07.059 --> 02:08.594
<i> That's why I can't give up.</i>

02:08.628 --> 02:11.631
<i> I got to do everything I can
to find him.</i>

02:11.664 --> 02:14.133
<i> That's...
that's why I'm here.</i>

02:14.166 --> 02:15.401
<i> That's what all this is for.</i>

02:15.434 --> 02:18.505
[FINGERS TAPPING RAPIDLY]

02:23.943 --> 02:26.679
[METAL CREAKING]

02:28.114 --> 02:29.382
[LOUD THUMPING]

02:31.216 --> 02:34.353
[INTENSE RATTLING]

02:34.387 --> 02:35.722
[SOBS]

02:36.588 --> 02:39.526
[GASPING]

02:42.328 --> 02:45.598
EDDIE: Customer support...

02:45.631 --> 02:47.167
representative.

02:48.000 --> 02:50.269
Representative!

02:50.303 --> 02:53.373
Yeah, I'd like to reopen
my account.

02:53.406 --> 02:55.307
Well, it's technically
my mom's account,

02:55.341 --> 02:57.443
but she's cool
adding me back on.

02:57.477 --> 02:59.044
Mom!

02:59.078 --> 03:00.245
They need to talk to you.

03:00.279 --> 03:01.880
[DOOR CREAKS, SLAMS]

03:01.914 --> 03:04.817
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

03:11.857 --> 03:14.561
[GRIMES'
"WE APPRECIATE POWER"]

03:21.968 --> 03:24.170
<i> ♪ We appreciate power</i>

03:24.203 --> 03:26.405
<i>♪ We appreciate power, power</i>

03:26.439 --> 03:29.875
<i> ♪ What will it take
to make you capitulate ♪</i>

03:29.909 --> 03:30.810
[MUSIC STOPS]

03:31.877 --> 03:34.781
[SILVERWARE CLATTERING]

03:36.049 --> 03:37.784
[TV PLAYING SOFTLY]

03:37.817 --> 03:39.185
What's up, Henry?

03:39.218 --> 03:40.452
WOMAN ON TV:
<i> Keep looking for his father</i>

03:40.486 --> 03:42.388
<i> and to come forward
with any information</i>

03:42.421 --> 03:44.623
<i> that might help authorities.</i>

03:44.656 --> 03:47.293
CLAY ON TV:
<i> My dad's not a quitter.</i>

03:47.326 --> 03:48.861
<i> He'd never run.</i>

03:48.895 --> 03:51.397
<i> And I know someone out there
knows something,</i>

03:51.431 --> 03:53.432
<i> knows what really happened
to him,</i>

03:53.465 --> 03:56.569
<i> and I'm not gonna stop
until the truth comes out.</i>

03:59.105 --> 04:00.907
<i> Whatever it takes.</i>

04:04.043 --> 04:05.644
[MUFFLED SPEECH]

04:05.678 --> 04:07.346
MAN:<i> Excuse me.</i>

04:07.380 --> 04:09.882
[DISHES CLATTERING]

04:09.915 --> 04:11.617
Uh, welcome to Surf N' Pizza,

04:11.651 --> 04:13.385
where we "surf up"
the best pizza

04:13.419 --> 04:14.687
in upstate New York.

04:14.720 --> 04:16.923
Hang loose,
and how can I help you today?

04:19.425 --> 04:22.562
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

04:28.934 --> 04:30.770
I know what I saw.

04:31.871 --> 04:33.740
MAN: We want to believe you,
Ms. Hulce.

04:33.773 --> 04:37.209
Trust us, the department's
suffered enough embarrassment.

04:37.243 --> 04:38.577
Were you drunk?

04:38.611 --> 04:39.812
I'm sorry?

04:39.845 --> 04:42.782
Or high, perhaps?

04:43.616 --> 04:45.485
Eight shots
from your service weapon.

04:45.518 --> 04:47.953
No body in the road,
though you called it in.

04:47.987 --> 04:49.688
No footprints,

04:49.722 --> 04:51.624
just you alone
on a country road.

04:51.657 --> 04:54.193
You were either intoxicated,
or you were hallucinating.

04:54.227 --> 04:55.894
I was not drunk.
I was not high.

04:55.928 --> 04:57.096
Sir,

04:57.129 --> 04:59.899
I know it might be difficult
for you to believe, but I...

04:59.932 --> 05:01.534
MAN: You know what you saw.

05:01.567 --> 05:02.835
Noted.

05:02.868 --> 05:05.905
This isn't the first time
you've been called
for review, correct?

05:07.440 --> 05:10.443
Is the Ortez Mackey case
relevant here?

05:11.977 --> 05:13.512
We'll have to see.

05:13.546 --> 05:15.781
But a situation like this
merits a second look.

05:15.814 --> 05:17.483
Now, is there anything
you'd like to say

05:17.516 --> 05:19.352
before we dig deeper?

05:22.855 --> 05:24.757
[PAPERS SHUFFLING]

05:24.790 --> 05:27.226
MAN:
Thank you for your candor.

05:27.259 --> 05:30.629
[DOOR OPENS]

05:30.662 --> 05:33.566
ANNA: I swear it's like
someone is fucking with me.

05:33.599 --> 05:35.434
FISHER: Why would anyone
in this quaint little town

05:35.467 --> 05:36.936
want to mess
with you, Sheriff?

05:36.969 --> 05:39.604
There's something deeper
going on with this
Bill Boone shit, I...

05:39.638 --> 05:42.107
Got to wait for the snow
to melt.

05:42.141 --> 05:45.778
If Bill was dumb enough
to escape through those woods,

05:45.811 --> 05:48.448
it's more than likely
somebody'll find his body
thawing out.

05:48.481 --> 05:50.783
No sense in us trying
to track him down
before then.

05:52.417 --> 05:55.621
At the Coles house,

05:55.655 --> 05:58.057
I found new blood evidence.

05:58.090 --> 05:59.959
What kind of new?

06:01.059 --> 06:02.294
Bill Boone's blood.

06:02.327 --> 06:04.296
In the dining room.

06:04.329 --> 06:06.132
You confirm that
with the lab?

06:06.999 --> 06:08.767
[SIREN WAILING DISTANTLY]

06:08.800 --> 06:10.068
Huh.

06:10.102 --> 06:13.706
Coles women
never said anything
about a struggle.

06:13.739 --> 06:15.441
Exactly.

06:15.474 --> 06:17.577
How come I didn't see
the blood report?

06:18.344 --> 06:19.778
[STAMMERS]

06:19.812 --> 06:23.383
Because I found it after
we wrapped the crime scene.

06:24.450 --> 06:26.552
I expedited the sample
to an independent lab.

06:27.653 --> 06:29.155
You broke chain of evidence?

06:29.188 --> 06:30.856
A new warrant
would've taken days.

06:30.890 --> 06:32.591
If the board finds out
about this

06:32.624 --> 06:35.094
after you went all Wyatt Earp
on your cruiser?

06:35.127 --> 06:36.628
Shit.

06:36.661 --> 06:38.764
Yeah, I know how it looks.
I...

06:38.798 --> 06:41.534
You sure you aren't
the person fucking with you?

06:42.701 --> 06:44.737
What are my options here?

06:44.770 --> 06:46.839
[SCOFFS]
To keep your job?

06:46.872 --> 06:49.141
[SIGHS]

06:49.175 --> 06:51.244
Cash in every favor you got.

06:51.277 --> 06:52.611
And then start praying

06:52.644 --> 06:54.814
to the holy patron saint
of kissing ass.

06:56.882 --> 07:01.119
I don't see
a button for that.

07:01.153 --> 07:03.455
Maybe the promotion expired?

07:03.489 --> 07:06.358
You new here?
You seem new.

07:06.392 --> 07:09.461
No, I've actually worked here
for 20 years.

07:09.495 --> 07:11.330
Try another one.

07:11.363 --> 07:12.631
Another what?

07:12.665 --> 07:13.965
Code.

07:13.999 --> 07:15.467
Hey, Janet.

07:15.501 --> 07:20.139
Oh. [CHUCKLES]
Grady, thank God.

07:20.172 --> 07:22.975
This girl can't seem to find
the discount code.

07:24.777 --> 07:26.379
All right, well, let's, uh...
let's see here.

07:26.412 --> 07:28.214
It's, uh, this button
right here.

07:28.247 --> 07:30.283
It says "My Favorite Customer."

07:28.247 --> 07:30.283
[REGISTER BEEPS]

07:30.316 --> 07:32.217
JANET: Oh, great.

07:32.251 --> 07:34.420
That'll be, uh,
$26.53, please.

07:34.453 --> 07:36.555
Finally. [CLEARS THROAT]

07:36.589 --> 07:38.490
Careful on those icy roads.

07:36.589 --> 07:38.490
Yes.

07:38.523 --> 07:39.558
You too, you too.

07:39.591 --> 07:41.393
Mm, ooh!
[CHUCKLES] Bye!

07:41.427 --> 07:43.829
Bye. See you.

07:43.863 --> 07:47.600
Yeah, she's at least top three
most horrible customers.

07:47.633 --> 07:50.236
I really hope I don't meet
the other two.

07:50.269 --> 07:52.071
I'm one of them, so...

07:52.104 --> 07:53.339
Are you?

07:52.104 --> 07:53.339
Yeah.

07:53.372 --> 07:55.274
You know,
that makes sense.

07:55.308 --> 07:57.877
You do seem terrible.

07:59.511 --> 08:02.714
Hey, so um, don't
get creeped out
or anything, but I just...

08:02.748 --> 08:03.949
do I...
do I know you?

08:03.982 --> 08:05.384
Like, I feel like I know you
from somewhere,

08:05.417 --> 08:06.451
and I'm just...
I'm just trying to place it.

08:06.485 --> 08:07.853
[BELL JINGLES]

08:06.485 --> 08:07.853
Um...

08:07.887 --> 08:09.822
You know...

08:07.887 --> 08:09.822
Oh, sorry. Later.

08:14.627 --> 08:16.595
Welcome to Surf N' Pizza,

08:16.629 --> 08:18.564
where we "surf up"
the best pizza

08:18.597 --> 08:19.865
in upstate New York.

08:19.898 --> 08:22.568
Hang loose,
and how can I help you today?

08:22.601 --> 08:25.270
We need to talk. Now.

08:25.304 --> 08:28.240
I'm at work.

08:28.274 --> 08:30.543
So take a break.

08:34.379 --> 08:36.782
Where are you
with the truck?

08:36.815 --> 08:38.851
Uh, I don't know.
Nowhere?

08:40.953 --> 08:42.354
I got in it,

08:42.388 --> 08:44.590
and then I was
instantly back

08:44.623 --> 08:47.592
at the trailer park, so...

08:47.626 --> 08:50.429
Yeah,
"nowhere" seems right.

08:50.463 --> 08:51.797
Well, you can't let
what's going on in your head

08:51.830 --> 08:53.432
control what happens
to your body.

08:53.465 --> 08:55.534
Oh, well, if that's all.

08:55.567 --> 08:57.236
You need
to get in the truck,

08:57.269 --> 08:58.537
control your emotions

08:58.570 --> 09:01.073
long enough
to stay in the truck.

09:01.106 --> 09:03.242
It's the only way
that this gets better.

09:03.275 --> 09:06.479
I'm sorry, what the fuck
do you think I've been doing?

09:06.512 --> 09:09.448
I spend every free
fucking moment I have

09:09.481 --> 09:13.919
in that stupid garage,
so I just...

09:13.952 --> 09:15.121
I can't.

09:15.154 --> 09:19.491
I... I didn't...
I did not ask for this.

09:19.524 --> 09:22.695
It's unfair, I know.

09:24.596 --> 09:27.066
No one gave us that choice.

09:30.569 --> 09:32.404
My break's over.

09:32.438 --> 09:34.173
Henry.

09:34.206 --> 09:36.475
Meet me at the garage tomorrow.

09:36.508 --> 09:37.877
We'll do this together.

09:39.145 --> 09:42.048
[DARK HORSES' "ALONE"]

09:47.186 --> 09:48.921
<i> ♪ He called the shots</i>

09:48.954 --> 09:51.123
<i>♪ He called the angry shots</i>

09:53.859 --> 09:56.228
<i> ♪ He lost his nerve</i>

09:56.261 --> 09:58.130
<i> ♪ He lost his whole world</i>

10:01.533 --> 10:03.369
<i> ♪ He could not speak</i>

10:03.402 --> 10:05.838
<i> ♪ For he might fail her ♪</i>

10:15.347 --> 10:18.117
[HORN BLARING]

10:24.022 --> 10:25.691
[GRUNTS]

10:28.126 --> 10:29.561
[GROANS]

10:29.595 --> 10:31.397
[MUSIC FADES]

10:34.399 --> 10:36.335
[SIGHS]

10:37.936 --> 10:39.571
JENNA:
This one's interesting.

10:39.604 --> 10:41.339
THOMAS:
I could see you there.

10:41.373 --> 10:42.807
Hey, hon,
we got lots of extras

10:42.841 --> 10:44.376
from the college fair,
for Henry.

10:44.410 --> 10:46.212
Oh, sure.

10:47.580 --> 10:49.448
Is this the school
that you're gonna visit?

10:49.481 --> 10:50.482
It's a pretty campus.

10:50.515 --> 10:52.885
Oh, no,
that's one of my backups.

10:52.918 --> 10:54.754
Uh, this is where we're going.

10:54.787 --> 10:57.723
Colgate.
Megan's giving us a tour.

10:57.756 --> 11:01.026
It's not MIT, but they have
a strong bio program.

11:01.060 --> 11:01.994
[DOOR CLOSES]

11:02.027 --> 11:03.195
Here's one
from a good art school.

11:03.228 --> 11:06.565
Maybe Henry
can get her groove on there.

11:06.599 --> 11:08.901
Hey, honey, how was work?

11:06.599 --> 11:08.901
So much fun.

11:08.934 --> 11:11.003
Hey, what'd your boss say?

11:12.271 --> 11:13.939
About taking the weekend off

11:13.972 --> 11:16.308
to visit Colgate with me
and Townes.

11:16.341 --> 11:18.944
I forgot to ask.

11:20.512 --> 11:21.981
That's okay.

11:22.014 --> 11:24.684
We could all go together
and look at schools
in the spring.

11:24.717 --> 11:26.151
Make a trip out of it.

11:24.717 --> 11:26.151
Henry, are you bleeding?

11:26.185 --> 11:28.387
Yeah, I just crashed my bike,
but it's not a big deal.

11:28.420 --> 11:29.821
CLEO: Why didn't you call us?

11:29.855 --> 11:31.523
One of us
would have picked you up.

11:31.557 --> 11:33.224
It's fine.

11:33.258 --> 11:34.694
CLEO: Hey...

11:36.595 --> 11:37.929
Henry, wait.

11:36.595 --> 11:37.929
Mom, it's fine.

11:37.963 --> 11:39.765
I just want to go to bed.

11:39.798 --> 11:42.667
I don't want you
riding your bike
to that pizza place.

11:42.701 --> 11:44.736
It's too far.

11:44.769 --> 11:47.706
From here on,
you need to ask for a ride.

11:47.739 --> 11:49.207
Are you fucking serious?

11:49.241 --> 11:50.409
Henry.

11:50.442 --> 11:52.645
I got this job to help out,
now I'm being
punished for it?

11:52.678 --> 11:56.048
This is about your safety.
You're out there alone.
Something could happen.

11:59.685 --> 12:01.420
What's gonna happen
to me, Mom?

12:03.722 --> 12:05.590
Right. Great.

12:05.624 --> 12:07.826
Good talk.

12:07.859 --> 12:10.930
[MIYNT'S
"AFTER THE GOLD RUSH"]

12:13.632 --> 12:18.003
<i> ♪ So you keep dreaming
of a better day</i>

12:19.371 --> 12:25.110
<i> ♪ You know for me
there's no replacement</i>

12:25.143 --> 12:29.014
<i> ♪ That's why for you
it is so hard to make... ♪</i>

12:29.047 --> 12:30.149
What?

12:30.182 --> 12:33.919
Did you really forget
to ask off work?

12:36.488 --> 12:38.424
Does it matter?

12:38.457 --> 12:43.195
I know that you're dealing
with this job
and school and...

12:44.396 --> 12:45.564
everything,

12:45.597 --> 12:48.700
but maybe
getting out of Reston
would be good for you.

12:48.734 --> 12:50.169
What are you doing?

12:51.303 --> 12:52.571
What do you mean?

12:52.604 --> 12:56.842
You want to go to Colgate
and major in biology
or whatever?

12:56.875 --> 12:58.344
That's fucking great.
Awesome.

12:58.377 --> 13:01.580
I'm glad that you get
to plan your life out
so perfectly.

13:01.613 --> 13:04.516
But you don't need
to come up here
and rub it in.

13:04.549 --> 13:05.818
That's not what I'm doing.

13:07.553 --> 13:09.255
Don't you have a suitcase
to pack?

13:09.855 --> 13:12.324
I got this for you.

13:17.663 --> 13:20.566
[FOOTSTEPS DESCENDING]

13:43.388 --> 13:46.258
[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

13:48.761 --> 13:50.062
Hey.

13:53.265 --> 13:55.167
Meet at your house
after school?

13:55.200 --> 13:57.469
Yes,
but if you are late,

13:57.502 --> 13:59.171
I will leave without you.

13:59.204 --> 14:01.740
The only reason you're
accompanying me on this trip

14:01.773 --> 14:06.278
is because my parents
don't like me driving
long distances by myself.

14:06.311 --> 14:08.614
If it were up to me,
I would go alone.

14:08.647 --> 14:10.515
[LOCKER SLAMS]

14:10.549 --> 14:12.851
Oh.

14:10.549 --> 14:12.851
Pack one bag.

14:12.884 --> 14:14.486
Megan's dorm room is small.

14:14.519 --> 14:16.989
And no music in the car.

14:17.022 --> 14:19.558
Or food.
Plan your meals accordingly.

14:19.591 --> 14:22.861
Townes, are you okay?
Why are you being like this?

14:22.895 --> 14:24.964
[STAMMERS]

14:24.997 --> 14:26.831
I'm... I'm not being
like anything.

14:26.865 --> 14:29.568
I'm... I'm simply
stating facts.

14:29.601 --> 14:31.370
[LOCKER CLATTERS]

14:33.905 --> 14:36.775
NIKOLAI: Have you ever seen
<i> Mork & Mindy?</i>

14:36.808 --> 14:39.011
It's about an alien
that comes to Earth.

14:39.044 --> 14:42.914
It was one of the only
American shows
on TV in Romania.

14:42.947 --> 14:44.550
[STOPWATCH BEEPS]

14:47.352 --> 14:51.623
It's how I learned English,
for the most part.

14:51.657 --> 14:54.626
The alien had
this catchphrase,

14:54.659 --> 14:56.394
"Nanu-Nanu."

14:56.428 --> 14:59.865
For a long time, I thought
that's how Americans
greeted each other.

14:59.898 --> 15:01.567
Are you having a stroke?

15:03.001 --> 15:04.903
Just a story.

15:04.936 --> 15:06.372
[STOPWATCH BEEPS]

15:08.840 --> 15:11.443
[SIGHS]

15:11.476 --> 15:12.678
Your turn.

15:15.747 --> 15:17.583
I mean, I don't
get what you want...

15:18.884 --> 15:20.386
Tell me a story.

15:22.854 --> 15:24.455
[EXHALES]

15:24.489 --> 15:27.191
Well, I'm supposed to be
in statistics right now,

15:27.225 --> 15:31.863
but instead,
I skipped school

15:31.897 --> 15:34.066
to hang out in lawn chairs

15:34.099 --> 15:38.403
with a 50... I don't know,
however-old-you-are man.

15:38.436 --> 15:39.338
[STOPWATCH BEEPS]

15:44.009 --> 15:46.078
What is this?
Are you trying
to distract me?

15:46.111 --> 15:50.115
No. Just reminding you,
you're a person who had a life
before what happened,

15:50.148 --> 15:51.650
and you'll have one after.

15:55.954 --> 15:59.058
[HENRY BREATHING DEEPLY]

16:00.592 --> 16:02.027
[STOPWATCH BEEPS]

16:06.231 --> 16:09.301
The first concert
I ever went to...

16:09.334 --> 16:10.636
Ramones.

16:10.669 --> 16:12.571
Auckland, 1989.

16:16.074 --> 16:18.977
Foo Fighters, fifth grade.

16:19.010 --> 16:20.446
[STOPWATCH BEEPS]

16:24.216 --> 16:27.018
My favorite holiday
as a kid was

16:27.052 --> 16:28.921
Sfantul Nicolae.

16:28.954 --> 16:30.955
St. Nicholas Day.

16:30.989 --> 16:32.657
He left chocolate
in our boots.

16:32.690 --> 16:35.527
Halloween, same reason.

16:35.560 --> 16:37.029
Without the boots.

16:38.764 --> 16:40.366
That's who
I was named after.

16:41.566 --> 16:42.534
A saint.

16:44.503 --> 16:47.573
When I was, like, 11,
my mom dated a guy named Henry.

16:48.807 --> 16:50.075
[STOPWATCH BEEPS]

16:51.876 --> 16:53.812
[NIKOLAI EXHALES]

16:53.846 --> 16:55.613
Before I came to Reston,
I would have said

16:55.647 --> 16:58.383
Primm, Nevada, was
the shittiest place on Earth.

16:58.416 --> 17:01.353
[LAUGHS]

17:05.256 --> 17:08.293
I once found this scratcher

17:08.326 --> 17:12.664
on the ground of this
crappy apartment complex

17:12.697 --> 17:15.300
where we used to live.

17:15.333 --> 17:18.537
I got 50 bucks,
and I paid off our gas bill.

17:21.172 --> 17:23.542
I've never won anything since.

17:25.177 --> 17:28.013
A friend of mine
once told me

17:28.046 --> 17:29.715
fish are supposed
to be lucky.

17:31.483 --> 17:32.751
I still believe him.

17:35.053 --> 17:36.555
[STOPWATCH BEEPS]

17:38.924 --> 17:41.060
[NIKOLAI SIGHS]

17:42.161 --> 17:44.696
You are more
than what happened
in this truck.

17:44.729 --> 17:47.666
[SOFT MUSIC]

17:48.901 --> 17:51.804
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

17:53.638 --> 17:56.542
[UNSETTLING MUSIC]

18:00.512 --> 18:02.481
[TRUCK RATTLING]

18:02.514 --> 18:04.382
[METAL CREAKING]

18:04.416 --> 18:07.952
Remember,
you're in control.

18:07.986 --> 18:10.722
[EXHALES]

18:10.756 --> 18:12.958
NIKOLAI:
You are making it move.

18:12.991 --> 18:14.960
I'm gonna get in, okay?

18:12.991 --> 18:14.960
[LIGHT BUZZES]

18:14.993 --> 18:16.995
Okay.

18:17.029 --> 18:21.467
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

18:21.500 --> 18:24.503
Tell me another story
about a time you felt safe.

18:25.737 --> 18:27.005
[CRASHING]

18:25.737 --> 18:27.005
I don't...

18:27.038 --> 18:28.640
Whatever pops into your head.

18:28.673 --> 18:30.742
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

18:30.775 --> 18:32.511
Um...

18:33.945 --> 18:35.914
me and my mom,
we were driving.

18:35.947 --> 18:37.115
[METAL CREAKING]

18:37.148 --> 18:38.750
There's a fair
on the side of the road.

18:38.783 --> 18:39.784
Okay.

18:39.818 --> 18:41.820
[EXHALES]

18:41.853 --> 18:45.090
There was a merry-go-round,
and...

18:45.123 --> 18:48.193
[INTENSE RATTLING]

18:48.227 --> 18:49.428
[SOFT SIZZLE]

18:49.461 --> 18:50.762
[LOW RUMBLING]

18:50.795 --> 18:51.929
[SEAT BELT CLICKS]

18:51.963 --> 18:53.932
It's, like,
really hot in here.

18:53.965 --> 18:55.200
[GLASS TINKLING]

18:55.234 --> 18:57.769
Claustrophobic.

18:57.802 --> 18:59.337
[METAL CREAKS]

18:59.371 --> 19:00.939
The fair was outside, right?

19:00.972 --> 19:03.107
It was in a field.

19:03.141 --> 19:05.510
Good. So...
so it was an open space.

19:05.544 --> 19:06.444
Open.

19:06.478 --> 19:07.979
[TINKLING]

19:06.478 --> 19:07.979
Like your hands.

19:08.013 --> 19:10.014
Open your hands.

19:08.013 --> 19:10.014
Okay.

19:10.048 --> 19:12.251
[RATTLING]

19:12.284 --> 19:14.553
HENRY: That hurt.

19:14.586 --> 19:15.687
[GRUNTS]

19:15.720 --> 19:17.289
I can't, I can't, I can't.
I can't. Fuck!

19:17.322 --> 19:19.257
I can't. I can't.
Fuck!

19:19.290 --> 19:23.194
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

19:23.227 --> 19:25.931
You sat in the truck

19:25.964 --> 19:27.899
for one minute
and 42 seconds,

19:27.932 --> 19:29.167
and you're still here.

19:29.201 --> 19:31.936
[GASPS]

19:29.201 --> 19:31.936
I know it's hard.

19:31.970 --> 19:33.672
The guilt.

19:33.705 --> 19:36.040
But it's not your fault.

19:36.074 --> 19:38.242
[GASPING]

19:38.276 --> 19:41.880
It's not your fault.

19:41.913 --> 19:43.281
[EXHALES SHAKILY]

19:43.315 --> 19:45.317
We'll try again tomorrow.

19:58.629 --> 20:00.265
[GRUNTS]

20:06.705 --> 20:08.940
Here.

20:08.973 --> 20:12.043
[IN ACCENT]
I am strong man,

20:12.076 --> 20:15.580
twisting cap off tiny bottle
for woman...

20:15.614 --> 20:19.350
who is looking at me
with such anger.

20:19.383 --> 20:21.018
[NORMAL VOICE]
What happened to your meds?

20:21.052 --> 20:24.422
They didn't give me
enough to start.
Refills are too expensive.

20:24.456 --> 20:28.660
No, I'm fine.
These are... extra strength.

20:29.828 --> 20:34.332
You know, your daughter
has her own pharmacy upstairs.

20:34.365 --> 20:36.301
Oh, my God,
could you imagine?

20:36.335 --> 20:37.402
I'm just saying.

20:37.435 --> 20:40.005
Hey, wait.
Where are you going?

20:40.038 --> 20:44.175
Stu threw me some shifts
for his plowing company, so...

20:44.209 --> 20:45.510
enjoy your peace and quiet.

20:45.544 --> 20:48.080
No, the peace and quiet
is driving me nuts.

20:48.113 --> 20:50.015
I'm just talking to myself
all day.

20:50.048 --> 20:52.217
Maybe we could get a dog
or something.

20:52.251 --> 20:54.619
You think talking to a dog
would feel different?

20:54.652 --> 20:56.621
I don't know.
I've only ever had a cat.

20:56.655 --> 20:58.256
But you know what,
the girls are gonna move out,

20:58.289 --> 21:00.291
and this place
is gonna be pretty quiet,

21:00.325 --> 21:01.659
so maybe we get a dog then.

21:01.693 --> 21:04.662
Well, that's assuming
Henry goes to college.

21:04.696 --> 21:06.431
Why wouldn't Henry
go to college?

21:06.465 --> 21:09.301
Well,
maybe she doesn't need it.

21:09.334 --> 21:12.136
She's... she's different.
She's smart.

21:12.170 --> 21:13.838
She could figure it out
on her own.

21:13.872 --> 21:16.808
Well... well, it's important.
She needs an education.

21:17.676 --> 21:20.379
Well,
if that's what she wants.

21:20.412 --> 21:22.013
So you don't want her
to succeed.

21:22.047 --> 21:24.849
It's hard
without a college degree.
You know that.

21:24.882 --> 21:26.851
Excuse me?

21:24.882 --> 21:26.851
I didn't mean it like that.

21:26.884 --> 21:29.787
I just want Henry to have
opportunities, that's all.

21:29.821 --> 21:31.122
Yeah, so do I.

21:31.155 --> 21:34.292
I am just saying that
Henry isn't self-motivated
like Jenna.

21:34.326 --> 21:37.629
You just... you got
to give her a push
in the right direction.

21:37.662 --> 21:40.899
So I got to push Henry
into college
so she can be more like Jenna

21:40.932 --> 21:43.335
so she doesn't end up
a failure like me?

21:43.368 --> 21:45.036
You know what I mean.

21:43.368 --> 21:45.036
No, clearly I don't.

21:45.069 --> 21:46.571
You know how Henry is.

21:46.604 --> 21:49.408
Apparently not, so please,
keep telling me
what my daughter needs.

21:49.441 --> 21:51.910
I can't do this now.
I got to go. We'll talk later.

21:51.943 --> 21:54.546
Yeah, fine, 'cause
you know what's best.

21:54.579 --> 21:56.648
[SIGHS]

21:59.918 --> 22:02.321
[DOOR SLAMS]

21:59.918 --> 22:02.321
[SIGHS]

22:03.922 --> 22:06.825
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

22:11.796 --> 22:13.698
[LAUGHTER,
INDISTINCT CHATTER]

22:13.732 --> 22:14.700
Hey.

22:25.110 --> 22:26.577
This is my bed.

22:26.611 --> 22:28.713
Well, it's actually
Tammy Cho's bed,

22:28.747 --> 22:31.849
but she's never here on account
of having two boyfriends,

22:31.883 --> 22:33.117
so when I visit,

22:33.151 --> 22:35.387
it's my bed.

22:37.622 --> 22:39.658
You'll sleep on the floor.

22:41.659 --> 22:44.062
[FRIDGE DOOR CREAKS OPEN,
CLOSES]

22:45.330 --> 22:47.732
Is that Megan's girlfriend?

22:47.765 --> 22:50.134
Darcy, yeah.

22:50.168 --> 22:51.770
How long have they
been together?

22:51.803 --> 22:52.771
Five months.

22:52.804 --> 22:53.838
I like her,

22:53.871 --> 22:56.775
so I don't mind
if they never break up.

22:58.276 --> 23:00.512
Megan brought her home
for Thanksgiving.

23:00.545 --> 23:03.848
Oh, so they're, like,
a real thing.

23:03.882 --> 23:07.452
Yes, but they're
not as serious
as Zoe and me.

23:07.486 --> 23:09.588
We've been together
over a year.

23:10.822 --> 23:14.059
But you still
haven't met yet.

23:14.092 --> 23:16.928
Obviously we've met.
We know each other very well.

23:16.961 --> 23:18.863
No, I mean face-to-face.

23:18.897 --> 23:21.399
That doesn't affect
how well we know each other

23:21.432 --> 23:23.634
or how...
how we feel about each other.

23:23.668 --> 23:25.971
How could that
possibly be true?

23:27.706 --> 23:30.008
You see Zach face-to-face
every day.

23:30.041 --> 23:31.443
How well do you know him?

23:32.143 --> 23:33.678
What's his favorite movie?

23:34.646 --> 23:37.215
Or his favorite color?

23:37.248 --> 23:38.717
What is his zodiac sign?

23:40.185 --> 23:41.253
That stuff doesn't matter.

23:41.286 --> 23:43.688
Okay, does Zach have
any allergies?

23:43.722 --> 23:46.458
Those matter.
They can be life-threatening.

23:47.592 --> 23:50.629
<i> The Dark Crystal,</i> yellow,
Gemini, walnuts.

23:50.662 --> 23:51.963
Okay, well, whatever.

23:51.996 --> 23:54.365
At least I know for sure
that Zach is a real person.

23:54.398 --> 23:56.000
For all you know,

23:56.034 --> 23:58.670
Zoe could be some crazy person
playing a trick on you.

23:58.703 --> 24:01.005
Everything that she says
could be a lie.

24:01.038 --> 24:03.441
Zoe... Zoe's not a liar.

24:03.474 --> 24:06.711
We...
what we have is special.

24:06.744 --> 24:07.845
We...

24:07.879 --> 24:11.683
We... we don't need
public displays of affection

24:11.716 --> 24:16.020
or... or some overcrowded dance
to prove we love each other.

24:16.053 --> 24:17.856
She's real!
She's real!

24:17.889 --> 24:19.491
Townes...

24:17.889 --> 24:19.491
TOWNES: She is real.

24:19.524 --> 24:21.726
Hi, guys.

24:19.524 --> 24:21.726
TOWNES: She's real!

24:21.759 --> 24:23.862
Townes?
You... you okay?

24:25.931 --> 24:28.733
I... I got your snacks.

24:25.931 --> 24:28.733
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

24:38.877 --> 24:40.011
You good?

24:45.149 --> 24:47.218
I'm glad you could come.

24:47.251 --> 24:50.088
I bet it's nice getting out
of Reston for a minute.

24:55.092 --> 24:56.895
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

25:08.039 --> 25:09.006
Mrs. Dale, hi.

25:09.040 --> 25:10.275
Please, come in.

25:21.919 --> 25:23.788
Have a seat
on the couch.

25:30.962 --> 25:32.296
[CLEARS THROAT]

25:32.330 --> 25:34.465
You bake?

25:34.499 --> 25:35.600
Yes.

25:35.633 --> 25:37.168
Yeah, well,

25:37.201 --> 25:41.005
I'm working to get
that handshake
from Paul Hollywood.

25:41.039 --> 25:43.874
You watch
<i> The Great British Bake Off?</i>

25:43.908 --> 25:45.310
No.

25:45.343 --> 25:46.444
[LIQUID POURING]

25:46.477 --> 25:49.147
[SETS TEAPOT DOWN]

25:49.180 --> 25:50.916
Okay, um...

25:52.750 --> 25:54.586
I owe you an apology.

25:55.953 --> 25:59.657
What I said to you
before, I...

25:59.691 --> 26:01.226
was out of line.

26:06.030 --> 26:09.334
I know that we both want
what is best for this town.

26:09.367 --> 26:12.737
Despite our differences,
I think we're on the same side.

26:12.771 --> 26:17.709
I heard about your troubles
at the station, Ms. Hulce.

26:17.742 --> 26:19.644
Is that why
you asked me here?

26:21.813 --> 26:24.316
Actually, I wanted to talk
about Bill Boone.

26:26.751 --> 26:29.954
When Bill cut his deal
with the DEA,

26:29.988 --> 26:32.424
your husband wasn't part
of his agreement.

26:32.457 --> 26:34.826
If he hadn't...

26:34.859 --> 26:36.761
passed away that day,

26:36.794 --> 26:38.396
he would have
gone to prison.

26:38.429 --> 26:40.098
Bill sold him out.

26:41.098 --> 26:44.602
I'm... I'm concerned
that my troubles

26:44.636 --> 26:48.305
might negatively affect
this investigation.

26:48.339 --> 26:50.675
Do you think
you're the only one
who could bring him in?

26:50.708 --> 26:52.843
I'm the only one
who is motivated.

26:52.877 --> 26:54.646
Bill has a lot of connections
in this town.

26:54.679 --> 26:56.013
He employed
a lot of people.

26:56.047 --> 26:58.316
Not everybody wants
to see him behind bars.

26:59.483 --> 27:01.819
[SCOFFS]

27:01.852 --> 27:03.954
It's cheap to use
my husband's death

27:03.988 --> 27:06.725
to leverage sympathy,
Ms. Hulce.

27:07.192 --> 27:09.226
Even for you.

27:09.260 --> 27:11.963
You must be desperate.

27:11.997 --> 27:13.464
[STAMMERS] Okay.

27:13.497 --> 27:14.832
Look, please, Mrs. Dale...

27:14.866 --> 27:16.033
But you were right.

27:16.066 --> 27:18.836
I do want what's best
for this town,

27:18.870 --> 27:22.640
and I'll make sure that
your replacement finds Bill...

27:22.673 --> 27:23.875
for both of us.

27:23.908 --> 27:25.609
[FOOTSTEPS DEPARTING]

27:25.643 --> 27:28.213
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

27:36.220 --> 27:37.522
Yahtzee!

27:37.555 --> 27:39.090
Shit. No Yahtzee.

27:37.555 --> 27:39.090
[TOWNES' WATCH BEEPS]

27:39.123 --> 27:41.593
I always say Yahtzee
preemptively,

27:41.626 --> 27:45.596
just in case, but mostly
because it annoys Townes.

27:45.630 --> 27:46.998
I have to go to bed.

27:48.032 --> 27:50.401
Townes,
we're still playing.

27:50.435 --> 27:52.103
I said
I have to go to bed.

27:53.738 --> 27:55.506
What about
best three out of five?

27:55.539 --> 27:57.075
That's what we always do.

27:57.108 --> 28:00.010
I'm at a ten and a half hour
sleep deficit this weekend,

28:00.044 --> 28:02.213
and I need to start
making up for it.

28:02.247 --> 28:03.948
But it's only 7:30.

28:03.981 --> 28:07.118
And I'd like to make up three
and a half of those hours.

28:07.151 --> 28:09.019
Townes, is...
is something wrong?

28:09.053 --> 28:11.956
I need to put
my pajamas on now.

28:12.724 --> 28:13.958
MEGAN: Okay.

28:13.991 --> 28:18.362
Uh, how about you catch up
on your sleep,

28:18.396 --> 28:21.866
and, Jenna Faith,
you can come with me
to Darcy's.

28:21.899 --> 28:23.634
She's having
some people over.

28:23.668 --> 28:26.070
Oh, uh, I...
I don't want to intrude.

28:26.103 --> 28:28.606
No, you're not.
It'll be fun, I promise.

28:28.640 --> 28:29.974
These are my people.

28:31.709 --> 28:33.378
Okay.

28:33.411 --> 28:35.046
Yeah.

28:33.411 --> 28:35.046
MEGAN: Cool.

28:35.080 --> 28:36.113
TOWNES: Cool.

28:36.147 --> 28:37.882
You sure you don't
need anything?

28:37.915 --> 28:40.885
I already told you
what I need.

28:40.918 --> 28:43.087
Tell Darcy I say hello.

28:43.120 --> 28:44.355
Okay.

28:47.224 --> 28:49.027
[DOOR OPENS]

28:53.364 --> 28:55.333
[DOOR CLOSES]

28:55.366 --> 28:58.269
[TENSE MUSIC]

29:19.323 --> 29:20.792
[BELL JINGLES]

29:20.825 --> 29:22.293
[CASH REGISTER BEEPING]

29:22.327 --> 29:24.829
[PHONE KEYS TAPPING]

29:26.363 --> 29:27.498
[PHONE CHIMES]

29:27.531 --> 29:29.968
So you get paid
to hang out?

29:30.001 --> 29:32.637
Nah, I like to think of it
like I'm on call.

29:32.670 --> 29:35.173
Like a fireman or an EMT,
something like that.

29:35.206 --> 29:36.173
[PHONE CHIMES]

29:36.207 --> 29:37.141
[KEYS TAPPING]

29:37.175 --> 29:39.410
That's a totally apt
comparison.

29:41.879 --> 29:43.648
[PHONE CHIMES]

29:43.681 --> 29:46.484
You want a pep-pep?
They're really yummy.

29:46.517 --> 29:48.286
I'm gonna pass.

29:50.287 --> 29:54.092
So I think I figured out
where I know you from.

29:54.125 --> 29:55.994
Yeah, you were
at some rich kid's party

29:56.027 --> 29:57.962
I delivered to, right?

29:57.995 --> 29:59.898
Um...

29:57.995 --> 29:59.898
You, um...

30:00.999 --> 30:03.501
You, uh...
you asked me for weed.

30:03.535 --> 30:07.004
I'm not really big
into parties.

30:07.037 --> 30:09.941
Okay.

30:07.037 --> 30:09.941
Or smoking, so...

30:10.908 --> 30:12.777
I think you got
the wrong girl.

30:12.810 --> 30:15.146
Yeah, my bad.
Here, try that.

30:15.679 --> 30:18.082
Oh, thank you.

30:18.116 --> 30:20.518
But you, uh...
you do go to Reston, right?

30:22.220 --> 30:24.521
Yeah.

30:22.220 --> 30:24.521
I went to Lincoln.

30:24.555 --> 30:26.723
Thank you for asking.

30:26.757 --> 30:28.926
I mean,
I only kind of hated it.

30:28.960 --> 30:30.361
And now I'm over at SUNY,

30:30.394 --> 30:34.198
but I'm saving up
to transfer out of state, so...

30:34.231 --> 30:36.500
[CHUCKLES] You're probably
wondering where, right?

30:36.534 --> 30:37.769
[LAUGHS]

30:36.534 --> 30:37.769
Yeah.

30:37.802 --> 30:39.236
I'm thinking
somewhere warm.

30:39.270 --> 30:42.306
You know, I'd love to say
California, but...

30:42.340 --> 30:45.075
I'll probably end up
in, like, Florida.

30:45.109 --> 30:46.677
You know,
off-brand California.

30:46.710 --> 30:49.380
Why dream big
when you can dream medium.

30:49.413 --> 30:52.217
Well, hey, what can I say?
You know, I'm a realist.

30:54.185 --> 30:57.221
What about you?

30:54.185 --> 30:57.221
What?

30:57.254 --> 30:58.689
Do you know where
you want to go?

30:58.723 --> 31:00.725
To school?

30:58.723 --> 31:00.725
Mm-hmm.

31:00.758 --> 31:02.527
Um...

31:04.929 --> 31:06.965
You know Colgate?

31:06.998 --> 31:08.232
I mean,
it's not my first choice,

31:08.265 --> 31:11.735
but they have a really
good biology program.

31:11.768 --> 31:13.137
Biology?

31:13.170 --> 31:14.438
Oh, that's...
I just...

31:14.471 --> 31:16.774
I didn't really
peg you as a science nerd.

31:16.808 --> 31:17.875
That's cool.

31:16.808 --> 31:17.875
Yeah.

31:17.909 --> 31:19.444
That's me.

31:23.881 --> 31:27.018
[SOFT MUSIC]

31:33.891 --> 31:35.894
[EXHALES]

31:38.529 --> 31:40.465
Okay, Henry.

31:53.344 --> 31:54.946
[DRAWER OPENS]

33:00.210 --> 33:02.746
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

33:00.210 --> 33:02.746
MEGAN: Oh, hey!

33:02.780 --> 33:05.583
Ahh! I thought
you couldn't come!

